p: In eucalyptus oil, eucalyptol (76.96%), an oxygenated monoterpene, was the most abundant compound, and only α-pinene (8.31%), β-pinene (1.54%), α-terpineol (1.47%), cis-limonene-oxide (1.28%), D-limonene (1.09%), p-cymene (1.02%) and (±)-linalool (0.05%) were present with more than 1% relative abundance. Others like terpinolene, isoamyl valerianate, α-campholenal, trans-limonene-oxide, trans-carveol and carvone also occurred in higher than 0.5% relative abundance ( Table S1). The 54 identified components represent 99.73% of the total eucalyptus oil blend.
